<dl id="n06043e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06043e">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06043e"> 43(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Papa, laisse nous</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Mais notre pr&eacute;sence seule g&ecirc;ne l&apos;enfant parce qu&apos;elle suffit &agrave; le rappeler &agrave; la r&eacute;alit&eacute;. J&apos;ai vu, s&apos;il m&apos;arrivait de p&eacute;n&eacute;trer dans quelque pi&egrave;ce o&ugrave; jouaient mes enfants, leur jeu cesser presque aussit&ocirc;t. Et Louise de dire alors, d&apos;un ton c&acirc;lin: &ldquo;<mark>Oh! papa ... laisse-nous!</mark>&rdquo; <font color="green">[But our presence alone hinders the child because it is enough to remind him of reality. I saw, if it happened to me to enter some room where my children played, their game cease almost immediately. And Louise then said, in a cuddly tone: &ldquo;Oh! Dad ... leave us!&rdquo;]</font> <small> Fr&eacute;d&eacute;ric Queyrat, <a name="FQLJ" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#FQLJ"><cite title="source">Les Jeux des Enfants</cite></a> (1920) 68</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
